      • connect

        void connect(java.lang.String address,
             java.lang.String name,
             java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> options)
        Initiate a connection to server (for centralized distribution) or peer (for decentralized distribution). Connection is keep alive until disconnect is called.
        Parameters:
        address - centralized server's address or peer's address
        name - identified client name (must be unique within the system)
        options - additional connecting options
